{
  "text": "For the data extraction process, we used a modified version of the critical appraisal tool (CAT). [CITATION_1] Our process and working definitions for the synthesis are shown in Box 2. First-order constructs were drawn from the information extracted during the critical appraisal process and were informed by the items on the amended CAT 32 (see Table 3 , Column 1). All papers, qualitative and quantitative, were appraised by the same method. These first-order constructs informed the development of our second-order constructs through interpretation and collation of themes from first-order constructs (see Table 3 , Columns 3 and 4).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "205401862"
